p: Of the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory, holding Terms at Seattle, for the County of King.
The People of the United States of America, to the Sheriff of King County Greeting:

We command you, that you have the body of Thomas Gilbert and Catharine Gilbert by you imprisoned and detained as it is said, together with the time and cause of such imprisonment and detention by whatsoever name said Thomas Gilbert and Catharine Gilbert shall be called or charged, before the HON. RICHARD A. JONES, Judge of the aforesaid Court at the Court House in the City of Seattle W.T. on June 27th 1888 at the hour of 8 30 oclock A.M. of said day to do and receive what shall then and there be considered concerning the said Thomas Gilbert and Catharine Gilbert And have you then and there this writ.
WITNESS THE HON. RICHARD A. JONES, Judge of said District Court, and the seal thereof this 26th day of June A.D. 1888
